metadata.label: abstract
metadata.value: Letter from C.R. Breckinridge the Commissioner to the Five Civilized Tribes to John H. Brown, notifying him that his application to be enrolled as a Cherokee Freedmen has been rejected. It notes that copies of the proceedings and the Commission's decision has been forwarded to his attorney, Edgar Smith of Vinita, Indian Territory, It ends by stating that the decision has been sent to the U.S. Secretary of Interior for his review and decision.
